            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-15T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">C.P.(Gen)Doc.1.C.1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article 44</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-07-29T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The military clauses of the various draft Treaties contain an Article prohibiting
                    the possession or construction of, or experiments with, self-propelled or guided
                    missiles and certain other arms (Art. 44 of the Treaty with Italy). These
                    Articles do not prohibit research dealing with the application of nuclear energy
                    to military purposes.</p>
                <p>In order to prohibit such research, the above-mentioned Article should be
                    completed by the following paragraph: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“She shall not, for military purposes, engage in research concerned with
                            the application or development of nuclear energy.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
